+\subsection{Hodge Decomposition and Topological Circulation Sectors}
+        \label{subsec:hodge_topological_circulation}
+
+        \textbf{[ORTHODOX VECTOR-CALCULUS FOUNDATION].}
+        On a smooth bounded domain \(\Omega\subset\mathbb R^3\), the space of
+        smooth vector fields decomposes orthogonally as
+        \begin{align}
+            VF(\Omega)
+            =
+            FK\oplus HK\oplus CG\oplus HG\oplus GG,
+            \label{eq:canon_hodge_five_way}
+        \end{align}
+        where
+        \begin{align}
+            FK&=
+            \{\nabla\cdot\mathbf V=0,\ \mathbf V\cdot\mathbf n=0,\\
+            \text{all interior fluxes}=0\},\\
+            HK&=
+            \{\nabla\cdot\mathbf V=0,\ \nabla\times\mathbf V=0,\\
+            \mathbf V\cdot\mathbf n=0\},\\
+            CG&=
+            \{\mathbf V=\nabla\phi,\ \nabla\cdot\mathbf V=0,\\
+            \text{all boundary fluxes}=0\},\\
+            HG&=
+            \{\mathbf V=\nabla\phi,\ \nabla\cdot\mathbf V=0,\\
+            \phi\text{ constant on each boundary component}\},\\
+            GG&=
+            \{\mathbf V=\nabla\phi,\ \phi|_{\partial\Omega}=0\}.
+            \label{eq:canon_hodge_subspaces}
+        \end{align}
+        The incompressible boundary-tangent sector is
+        \begin{align}
+            K(\Omega)=FK\oplus HK,
+            \label{eq:canon_fluid_knot_hodge_sector}
+        \end{align}
+        and
+        \begin{align}
+            HK
+            \cong
+            H_1(\Omega;\mathbb R)
+            \cong
+            H_2(\Omega,\partial\Omega;\mathbb R).
+            \label{eq:canon_harmonic_knot_homology}
+        \end{align}
+        Hence \(\dim HK\) is the total genus of the boundary
+        \cite{CantarellaDeTurckGluck2002Hodge}.
+
+        \textbf{[CANON / INTERPRETATION GUARD].}
+        Vorticity determines the fluxless/curl-bearing part but does not determine
+        the harmonic-knot circulation sector.  A ball has \(HK=0\); a solid torus
+        has \(\dim HK=1\).  This counts independent global circulation channels, not
+        particle species or knot type.
+
